<html
    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    xml:lang="en"
    lang="en"
    metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
    i18n:domain="launchpad">

<head>
    <title metal:fill-slot="title">Overview of Distributions in
    Launchpad</title>
    <!-- Plone style sheet -->
    <style type="text/css" media="screen">@import url(plone.css);</style>
</head>

<body>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

    <h1>Launchpad Distribution Management: All Distributions</h1>

    
        <p>This page shows all distributions that are registered in the
        Launchpad. Note that some of these distributions are "read-only", we
        monitor those distributions and present package information for them
        in Launchpad, but they cannot be altered or managed through the
        Launchpad. The Launchpad representations of those distributions
        might be out of date.</p>

    <table width="100%" class="listing rowNavigation">
        <tr>
            <th>Name</th>
            <th>Title</th>
            <th>Domain Name</th>
        </tr>
        <tr tal:repeat="distribution context"
            tal:attributes="onclick
                string:window.location='/distros/${distribution/name}'">
            <td>
                <a tal:content="distribution/name" 
	               tal:attributes="href
                       distribution/name">
	               distribution name
	            </a>
                <span tal:condition="python: distribution.name in ['redhat', 'debian', 'gentoo']">
                    *
                </span>
            </td>
            <td tal:content="distribution/title">
                distribution title
            </td>
            <td tal:content="distribution/domainname">
                domain.org
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table>    

    <div>
      <div style="float: right;">
        (<span tal:replace="view/count" />
        distributions in total)
      </div>
      <div style="float: left;">
        * read-only distribution.
      </div>
    </div>

</div>

</body>
</html>
